HEADWORD: Ascidioidea
<hw>As*cid`i*oid"e*a</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos>
<ety>[NL., fr. <ets>ascidium</ets> + <ets>-oid</ets>. See
<er>Ascidium</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A group of Tunicata,
often shaped like a two-necked bottle. The group includes, social, and
compound species. The gill is a netlike structure within the oral
aperture. The integument is usually leathery in texture. See
<xex>Illustration</xex> in Appendix.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

